"{\"uid\": \"rnz.co.nz-news-olympics-2024-524557-olympics-2024-grieving-family-hurt-by-police-officer-s-role-in-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByLayli Foroudi, Reuters  Tens of thousands of people packed Paris for the opening ceremony.Photo:FRANCOIS-XAVIER MARIT/AFP  A French police officer who fatally shot a teenager of Tunisian heritage during a traffic stop in 2021 was among BMX riders who took part in theParis Olympics opening ceremony, to the distress of the deceased teenager's family.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.627282206577677e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 61, \"end\": 66, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6842176798102979e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 127, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8858946780074757e-45, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 180, \"end\": 188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_people\", \"score\": 0.9999998122966821, \"rank\": 1.4460962233799082e-07, \"text\": \"Tunisian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisian_people\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999852479474073, \"rank\": 1.4749472839592998e-05, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Romain Devassine, 26, shot 19-year-old Soheil El Khalfaoui as he tried to drive off during a traffic stop in Marseille on 4 August 2021.\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999990400283, \"rank\": 9.598456471726086e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the past three years, the youngster's family have been pressing for justice and a murder investigation by Marseille justice authorities is ongoing.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999990400283, \"rank\": 9.598456471726086e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So when Soheil's aunt, Samia El Khalfaoui, saw Devassine on television as she watched the opening ceremony, the shock it delivered felt akin to \\\"a cold shower\\\".\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busia_District\", \"score\": 0.9870292156613839, \"rank\": 0.01314122964896173, \"text\": \"Samia\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busia_District\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busia_District\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:  \\\"I found it indecent, disrespectful.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was there, majestic on the stage in his Napoleon costume - it was as if he was mocking us,\\\" she told Reuters.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.165195510221954e-27, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.627282206577677e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Devassine and the Interior Ministry did not respond to requests for comment on Devassine's role in the fatal shooting or his participation in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9999986844104128, \"rank\": 1.3155914966650638e-06, \"text\": \"Interior Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"El Khalfaoui is one of more than 20 people who have been shot dead by French police since 2020, most of them Black or Arab men, according to a Reuters tally.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8858946780074757e-45, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999636374849821, \"rank\": 2.994336431873035e-05, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.627282206577677e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was thefatal shooting by police of Nahel Merzouk- a 17-year-old of North African heritage - in similar circumstances in a Paris suburb in 2023 thatsparked nationwide unrest and stirred deep-seated grievancesover neglect and discrimination among communities of immigrant descent.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999985302740129, \"rank\": 1.2241220051603446e-06, \"text\": \"North African\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1419, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6842176798102979e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A police watchdog report seen by Reuters shows that in questioning Devassine acknowledged he shot the teenager, saying that he did so to save his colleague's life.\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.627282206577677e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No charges have been brought against Devassine to date.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A French law introduced in 2017 allows police to use their firearms following a refusal to comply with a traffic stop if the driver is likely to pose a risk to their life or physical safety, or to other people's.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1800, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.586065329063, \"rank\": 0.7062887703648062, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony spanned the centre of Paris, with performers dancing on rooftops, bridges and boats.Photo:DAN MULLAN  Devassine published photos of the ceremony on his Instagram profile on 27 July.\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6842176798102979e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Divers_Alert_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0910978042663971e-15, \"text\": \"DAN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Divers_Alert_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Divers_Alert_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7581912964782003e-23, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was incredible to live this ceremony in the middle of the Seine with the boys,\\\" he wrote.\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999990402825518, \"rank\": 9.597180348119576e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They had not been able to perform their stunts live because of the heavy rain, he said.\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The footage that was shown on TV during the opening ceremony was recorded during the afternoon's training, according toLa Voix du Nordnewspaper.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 organisers said all performers were hired by a production agency.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.0060858095221883e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The most difficult thing is to think that three years have passed and he is doing his stunts on TV while the investigative judge still has not interrogated him - if the judge had done his work, he would not be on TV,\\\" said Issam El Khalfaoui, Soheil's father.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Marseille prosecutor's office declined to comment.\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2886, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999990400283, \"rank\": 9.598456471726086e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The family's lawyer, Arie Alimi, said that Devassine was still working as a police officer.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is a sign that the Interior Ministry showcases authors of police violence,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3054, \"end\": 3071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9999986844104128, \"rank\": 1.3155914966650638e-06, \"text\": \"Interior Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Interior Ministry did not respond to a Reuters request for confirmation Devassine was a serving officer or to Alimi's allegation it was showcasing police violence.\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3125, \"end\": 3142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9999986844104128, \"rank\": 1.3155914966650638e-06, \"text\": \"Interior Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 3164, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.627282206577677e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Reuters  Copyright \\u00a92024,Radio New Zealand  \\\"My God.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3317, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"score\": 0.99999767246525, \"rank\": 2.3275400779111107e-06, \"text\": \"Radio New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's crazy,\\\" one French gold medallist said of the fan support at her venue in the heart of Paris.\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3362, \"end\": 3368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9995673522518916, \"rank\": 0.000432291050723195, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3437, \"end\": 3442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6842176798102979e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A French DJ who performed during the Paris Olympics' opening ceremony has filed a legal complaint after receiving abuse online.\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3447, \"end\": 3453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9995673522518916, \"rank\": 0.000432291050723195, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A sketch that saw drag queens and a naked singer interpret a biblical scene was never meant to disrespect, organisers say.\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch: From divas to Moulin Rouge can-can dancers, boats, an aircraft flyover - This year's high-energy, rain-soaked opening had it all.\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3719, \"end\": 3731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.384564508124472e-28, \"text\": \"Moulin Rouge\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_Rouge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A French policeman has been charged with homicide and is in custody over the killing of a teenager near Paris.\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9995673522518916, \"rank\": 0.000432291050723195, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3940, \"end\": 3945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6842176798102979e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"for ad-free news and current affairs  Olympics 2024 RSS  Follow RNZ News\", \"from\": 3948, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4000, \"end\": 4003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rashtriya_Swayamsevak_Sangh\", \"score\": 0.9548079211196369, \"rank\": 0.046881712860826485, \"text\": \"RSS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rashtriya_Swayamsevak_Sangh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rashtriya_Swayamsevak_Sangh\"}, {\"begin\": 4012, \"end\": 4015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RNZ\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_New_Zealand\"}]}]}"